article.headline: Chicago St 62, Detroit 47
article.story: CHICAGO (AP) -- Tony Weeden had 20 points Thursday to lead Chicago State to a 62-47 win over Detroit Mercy. Weeden made 7-of-14 shots from the field and finished with three 3-pointers. Deji Akindele added 12 points and 14 rebounds for the Cougars (1-7), who broke an eight-game losing streak that dated back to last season. Brandon Cotton had 12 points and Torvoris Baker added 11 points and 11 rebounds for Detroit Mercy (3-7). The Titans held a 37-27 advantage in rebounds, but made just 2-of 13 from 3-point range and had 20 turnovers.
